## My process

Yeah After writing the html document, I added the css style making the body of min-height of 100vh in other to keep it static I also flexed the body and justify it content to make the main element centered then i added the animation for the dice after styling it. Then to the Javascript I called the advicetext which i had wrapped in a span element which is in a paragraph element with appostrophe thus keeping the appostrophe constant no matter the advice generated. I linked to the api, collected it slip object which returnes an id and advice afterward i just changed the span element inner content once the dice is clicked

### Built with

- Semantic HTML5 markup
- CSS animation
- CSS custom properties
- Flexbox
- Javascript api

### What I learned

I have learned more about api by building this project. Yeah I know about json and fetching data from it but this app has enabled my interact with an api and be able to build something with it
